  "steps": [
    {
      "id": "l2-numbers-theory",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "Numbers 1 to 10",
      "body": "# Numbers 1–10\n\n| German | English |\n|---|---|\n| **eins** | one |\n| **zwei** | two |\n| **drei** | three |\n| **vier** | four |\n| **fünf** | five |\n| **sechs** | six |\n| **sieben** | seven |\n| **acht** | eight |\n| **neun** | nine |\n| **zehn** | ten |\n\nWatch the spelling: **fünf** has an **ü**. When counting, \"one\" is **eins**, but before a noun it becomes **ein/eine** (e.g. *ein Auto* — a car)."
    },
    {
      "id": "l2-ex-match-numbers-low",
      "type": "exercise",
      "title": "Match numbers 1–5",
      "exercise": {
        "id": "l2-ex-match-numbers-low",
        "type": "matching",
        "prompt": "Match each German number with its English meaning.",
        "card_ids": ["de-eins", "de-zwei", "de-drei", "de-vier", "de-fuenf"],
        "pairs": [
          {"left": "eins", "right": "one"},
          {"left": "zwei", "right": "two"},
          {"left": "drei", "right": "three"},
          {"left": "vier", "right": "four"},
          {"left": "fünf", "right": "five"}
        ],
        "direction": "target_to_source"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "l2-ex-match-numbers-high",
      "type": "exercise",
      "title": "Match numbers 6–10",
      "exercise": {
        "id": "l2-ex-match-numbers-high",
        "type": "matching",
        "prompt": "Match each German number with its English meaning.",
        "card_ids": ["de-sechs", "de-sieben", "de-acht", "de-neun", "de-zehn"],
        "pairs": [
          {"left": "sechs", "right": "six"},
          {"left": "sieben", "right": "seven"},
          {"left": "acht", "right": "eight"},
          {"left": "neun", "right": "nine"},
          {"left": "zehn", "right": "ten"}
        ],
        "direction": "target_to_source"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "l2-ex-free-three",
      "type": "exercise",
      "title": "Write the number",
      "exercise": {
        "id": "l2-ex-free-three",
        "type": "free_text",
        "prompt": "Write the German word for \"three\".",
        "card_ids": ["de-drei"],
        "accept": ["drei", "Drei"],
        "distractors": ["zwei", "vier", "zehn"],
        "hint": "The number 3.",
        "direction": "source_to_target"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "l2-ex-free-seven",
      "type": "exercise",
      "title": "Write the number",
      "exercise": {
        "id": "l2-ex-free-seven",
        "type": "free_text",
        "prompt": "Write the German word for \"seven\".",
        "card_ids": ["de-sieben"],
        "accept": ["sieben", "Sieben"],
        "distractors": ["sechs", "neun", "acht"],
        "hint": "The number 7.",
        "direction": "source_to_target"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "l2-colours-theory",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "Colours",
      "body": "# Colours\n\n- **rot** — red\n- **blau** — blue\n- **grün** — green\n- **gelb** — yellow\n- **schwarz** — black\n- **weiß** — white\n\nWatch the spelling of **grün** (with **ü**) and **weiß** (with **ß**). In German the colour word usually comes **before** the noun, like in English: *ein rotes Auto* — a red car."
    },
    {
      "id": "l2-ex-match-colours",
      "type": "exercise",
      "title": "Match the colours",
      "exercise": {
        "id": "l2-ex-match-colours",
        "type": "matching",
        "prompt": "Match each German colour with its English meaning.",
        "card_ids": ["de-rot", "de-blau", "de-gruen", "de-gelb"],
        "pairs": [
          {"left": "rot", "right": "red"},
          {"left": "blau", "right": "blue"},
          {"left": "grün", "right": "green"},
          {"left": "gelb", "right": "yellow"}
        ],
        "direction": "target_to_source"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "l2-ex-cloze-white",
      "type": "exercise",
      "title": "Complete the colour",
      "exercise": {
        "id": "l2-ex-cloze-white",
        "type": "cloze",
        "prompt": "Fill in the German colour for \"white\".",
        "card_ids": ["de-weiss"],
        "sentence": "Schnee ist ___ . (Snow is white.)",
        "blanks": [{"accept": ["weiß", "weiss"]}],
        "cloze_mode": "type",
        "hint": "Written with **ß**."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "l2-ex-cloze-black",
      "type": "exercise",
      "title": "Complete the colour",
      "exercise": {
        "id": "l2-ex-cloze-black",
        "type": "cloze",
        "prompt": "Fill in the German colour for \"black\".",
        "card_ids": ["de-schwarz"],
        "sentence": "Die Nacht ist ___ . (The night is black.)",
        "blanks": [{"accept": ["schwarz", "Schwarz"]}],
        "cloze_mode": "type",
        "hint": "Starts with *schw-*."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "l2-ex-tiles-redcar",
      "type": "exercise",
      "title": "Build a phrase",
      "exercise": {
        "id": "l2-ex-tiles-redcar",
        "type": "word_tiles",
        "prompt": "Arrange the tiles to mean \"a red car\".",
        "card_ids": ["de-rot"],
        "tiles": ["ein", "rotes", "Auto"],
        "hint": "Colour comes before the noun.",
        "direction": "source_to_target"
      }
    }
  ]
